The definition of `DifferentiableOn ℂ f s` is `∀ x ∈ s, HasDerAt ℂ f (fderiv ℂ f x) x`.
The definition of `HasDerAt ℂ f hf x` is `HasDerAt f hf x` (real differentiability) and `hf` is complex-linear.

So `Holo(Φ₅' r)` means `DifferentiableOn ℂ Φ₅' ℍ₀`. This implies `DifferentiableOn ℝ Φ₅' ℍ₀` because real differentiability is a necessary condition for complex differentiability.

